result.description:
Launch either a single sub-flow multiple times, or different sub-flows, all in parallel.

The preferred usage is to provide a WorkflowCoordinator object as the input variable named 'inputs'.   

The activity will first look in the workflow scratchpad for an object with the name provided and if not found will check for it as a global variable.

An alternative usage would be to provide a workflow (name or sys_id) and an array of input variables. 
In this case, a workflow name or ID must be provided.

Both parameters are object names but can be derived from scripts by using the javascript: prefix:

// in this example, a factory provides an appropriate WorkflowCoordinator instance which is pre-populated with 
// input variables, and information about which workflow(s) to run.  The workflow field is not used. since this information
// is provided by the coordinator.
//
INPUTS: ${ WorkflowFactory.getChangeManagementWorkflow(current) };



// in this example a Javascript class named MyWorkflowInputs returns an array of input vars and a workflow name 
// from two separate static methods
//
INPUTS:  ${ MyWorkflowInputs.getInputs() }
WORKFLOW: ${ MyWorkflowInputs.getWorkflow() }
